results.description:
“Erindale” 31 Reids Lane, Tawonga, Victoria

115ha (284 Acres)
Highly productive/genuine cattle breeding, cattle fattening country, plus horticulture/viticulture potential.

“Erindale” Location
Central to the Upper Kiewa Valley Region being only 5kms from Tawonga, 15kms to Mt Beauty, the gateway to the Australian Alps and the renowned snow/the ski fields of the Falls Creek Snow Resort. A comfortable 1 hour drive from Albury Wodonga (75kms) and all these regional cities have to offer. “Erindale” has a long frontage to Redbank Road and direct access to the crystal clean Kiewa River. A most attractive beautiful area with views to Mt Bogong.

“Erindale” Country divides into three distinct categories being approx 60ha (150 Acres) of prime loam soils with areas of alluvial creek flats approx 40ha (100 Acres) of sound low hill grazing pasture country and some 15ha (37 Acres) of steeper country with some light bush. Well balanced grazing country with a suggested stocking rate of 100 cows & calves on their equivalent.

“Erindale” Pasture, Fencing, Water
Some 90ha (220 Acres) has been sown to perennial pasture of phalaris, clovers, cocksfoot and rye grass species.
Fertiliser has been applied over most of the property on a regular basis. Fencing is in good order with some twenty (20) individual paddocks. Water to all paddocks either by dams, creeks or troughs. The water supply in general is excellent with 14 dams, permanent Wallaby Creek throughout the property and stock and domestic water licence and services the troughing and back up for the house & surrounds. Feature tree lines exist along fence lines and water ways with Blue Gum reserve along the Wallaby Creek.

“Erindale” working improvements include large (4 bay) machinery shed, with power. Two (2) hay sheds. Disused dairy and piggery plus cattle yards.

“Erindale” home & surrounds, gardens
The main feature of the home is a large hexagonal living room with large picture windows to take in the views of the valley and an eighteen foot vaulted timber ceiling.

This room leads to a meals/dining area adjacent to the modern, well appointed Baltic Pine kitchen. This kitchen has an abundance of drawers and cupboards, a large pantry, new electric oven, electric hot plates and a double sink.

The large laundry has built in cupboards and the two-way toilet leads from the laundry to the family bathroom. The home has four (4) bedrooms. The master bedroom is spacious with built in robes and an overhead fan. The other bedrooms have built in robes and overhead fans.

There is a single lock up garage under roof. Heating is via slow combustion wood heating plus zoned floor heating.

The garden at “Erindale” has been lovingly created by our current vendor and can only be described as a magnificent country garden. This garden has hosted many open garden days and could be one of the most attractive in the area.

This little piece of paradise is set on approximately 8 hectares (2 acres) and has been designed to take advantage of the picturesque views of the Upper Kiewa Valley through to Mt Bogong.

With many garden “rooms” and spacious lawn areas it can be used for entertainment all year round.

Many and varied established trees include liquid ambers, silver birches, maples, an oak tree plus many large gums. Azaleas, Camelias, Hydrangeas, Crepe Myrtles and “cottage” garden beds are scattered throughout.

A fishpond, paved areas made from old bricks from the property and rock edging all complete this attractive picture. A watering system throughout makes for ease of care.


Summary
“Erindale” is a complete smaller farm capable of supporting 100 cows & calves. “Erindale” also has potential for a variance of other rural activities similar those already in the area. Horticulture, viticulture, etc. “Erindale” combines good productivity with an excellent rural lifestyle and easy access to the over expanding tourist enterprises of the area.

With River Frontage the length of the property and situated on the same stretch of river as the Tawonga Caravan Park this property is totally unique.

Just over 7 hectares of land that has previously been used as a crusher plant this property has a large dam, access roads throughout and a large shed. The land is also relatively flat.

This property is Zoned Farming Land.

In the quiet and serenity of the Kiewa Valley, surrounded by
Mountains with farming land on one side and the river on the other you also have bitumen road access and an easy drive into town..

This property is a dream!
